==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Norm
<hw>Norm</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>norma</ets> a
rule. See <er>Normal</er>, <pos>a.</pos>]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A rule or authoritative standard; a model; a type;
<as>as, deviations from the <ex>norm</ex> are not
tolerated</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>A typical, structural unit; a
type.</def> <rj><au>Agassiz.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Norma</ent>⟦br⟧
